#000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">is Abraham Sh=
afi</a>:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">SoftBank sued former I=
RL CEO Abraham Shafi and five siblings and cousins for allegedly misleading=
 the investor about the messaging app=E2=80=99s growth, prompting the Japan=
ese conglomerate to buy $150 million worth of shares in the company in 2021=
 at the height of a pandemic-fueled consumer internet boom.</p><p style=3D"=
margin: 16px 0;">SoftBank said Shafi and his family members defrauded inves=
tors by lying about the company=E2=80=99s millions of users, which were act=
ually bots. The lawsuit said the defendants deleted data and communications=
 about the fraud after U.S. securities regulators began investigating the c=
ompany following a report in The Information questioning the user figures. =
Last month, The Information reported the company was being shut down follow=
ing an external investigation initiated by its board of directors that foun=
d 95% of its users were fake.</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=
Oops! I guess the ironic name makes it a bit funnier.=C2=A0A lot of tech fo=
unders saw the sort of story that unlocked SoftBank money and had <a href=
=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/32321698.266412/aHR0cHM6L=
y93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMDEtMTkvd2FzaGluZy13=
ZWIzP2NtcGlkPUJCRDA4MDcyM19NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJ=
jZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIzMDgwNyZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607=
f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB615e6360" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemsco=
pe" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !impor=
tant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom=
-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> ideas of roughly the form</a> =E2=
=80=9Cif I offer a good product at much less than my cost of producing it, =
I will attract a lot of users very quickly, and though I will lose money on=
 every transaction, SoftBank doesn=E2=80=99t care, they=E2=80=99ll give me =
tons of money anyway, and then the whole losing money thing is their proble=
m.=E2=80=9D If you have a company that is rapidly adding users but losing m=
oney on every one of them, you can either do the hard business work of impr=
oving your unit economics, or the easy financing work of meeting with Masay=
oshi Son for 20 minutes and acting crazy so he gives you a billion dollars.=
 After you have the billion dollars the unit economics don=E2=80=99t matter=
 so much. For you I mean.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But Shafi, allege=
dly, learned a much simpler lesson from SoftBank=E2=80=99s largesse, basica=
lly of the form =E2=80=9Cif I write a pitch deck showing that my user base =
is=C2=A0growing very rapidly, I don=E2=80=99t need anything else=E2=80=9D: =
Others hacked SoftBank=E2=80=99s algorithm by creating real but money-losin=
g user growth; IRL allegedly hacked SoftBank=E2=80=99s algorithm by creatin=
g fake user growth. Here are=C2=A0<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbus=
iness.com/click/32321698.266412/aHR0cHM6Ly9hc3NldHMuYndieC5pby9kb2N1bWVudHM=
vdXNlcnMvaXFqV0hCRmRmeElVL3JtV0U0ay5oNU5qYy92MA/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB69=
f6b6bf" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" st=
yle=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-widt=
h: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backgroun=
d-color: #ccc;">the complaint</a>=C2=A0and the <a href=3D"https://link.mail=
.bloombergbusiness.com/click/32321698.266412/aHR0cHM6Ly9uZXdzLmJsb29tYmVyZ2=
xhdy5jb20vYnVzaW5lc3MtYW5kLXByYWN0aWNlL3NvZnRiYW5rLWFsbGVnZXMtMTUwLW1pbGxpb=
24tbG9zcy1vbi1pcmwtc29jaWFsLWFwcC1jb2xsYXBzZQ/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBc779=
3652" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" styl=
e=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width:=
 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-=
color: #ccc;">Bloomberg story</a>=C2=A0that first reported=C2=A0it. From th=
e complaint:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In April 2021, Get=
 Together Inc. (a.k.a., =E2=80=9CIn Real Life,=E2=80=9D or =E2=80=9CIRL=E2=
=80=9D) seemingly was one of the fastest growing social media apps for Gene=
ration Z. According to IRL=E2=80=99s CEO Abraham Shafi, IRL=E2=80=99s mobil=
e app already had been downloaded by 25% of US Teens under 18 years old; IR=
L had 12 million monthly active users (=E2=80=9CMAUs=E2=80=9D); and IRL was=
 growing at a =E2=80=9Cmeteoric=E2=80=9D 400% year-over-year rate. Addition=
ally, IRL reported strong user engagement and retention metrics, which show=
ed that nearly 30% of its MAUs were using the platform on a daily basis. ..=
.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Through these metrics, IRL appeared to al=
ready be achieving network effects, and was well positioned for further vir=
al growth=E2=80=94similar to that which drove the emergence of today=E2=80=
=99s=C2=A0largest social media companies. Based on the data regarding activ=
e users and organic growth that IRL and Abraham Shafi presented to SoftBank=
, IRL convinced SoftBank that a capital infusion would allow IRL to further=
 increase its=C2=A0already-impressive rate of growth and monetize its enthu=
siastic user base.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">On May 18, 2021, SoftBan=
k paid $150 million to purchase IRL shares; both directly from IRL and from=
 individual holders of IRL shares. =E2=80=A6</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;=
">At the time of SoftBank=E2=80=99s investment, IRL was funneling tens of t=
housands of dollars to proxy services to enable an army of =E2=80=9Cbots,=
=E2=80=9D the entire purpose of which was to make IRL appear to be a thrivi=
ng social media site while Defendants orchestrated an elaborate scheme to d=
efraud investors. IRL also paid hundreds of thousands of dollars monthly to=
 a firm (the =E2=80=9CAgency=E2=80=9D) secretly operated by IRL=E2=80=99s o=
wn Head of Growth, in a coordinated scheme to conceal IRL=E2=80=99s user ac=
quisition costs and further IRL=E2=80=99s image as a thriving social media =
app.=C2=A0</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">There are some grea=
t operational details, like how another tech CEO noticed that IRL was swamp=
ed with bots and let them know about it, not understanding that that was th=
e point:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Some third-party vendo=
rs that routinely interacted with IRL began to notice bots on the platform.=
 On March 16, 2021, less than a month before the Series C discussions with =
SoftBank commenced, a CEO of another tech company noted in an email to Abra=
ham Shafi that =E2=80=9CIRL got hit by a massive bot attack generating mill=
ions of fake groups to join.=E2=80=9D But a supposed bot =E2=80=9Cattack=E2=
=80=9D was not news to Abraham Shafi and it was not an =E2=80=9Cattack=E2=
=80=9D at all; Abraham Shafi was actively working with Defendants to bring =
bots to IRL.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Abraham Shafi boasted about IR=
L=E2=80=99s sudden user increase the very next day. On March 17, 2021, Abra=
ham Shafi received an email from an investment firm who was impressed with =
IRL=E2=80=99s meteoric buildup of active users: =E2=80=9CWhat=E2=80=99s hap=
pened with DAUs recently? Whoa.=E2=80=9D In response, Abraham Shafi falsely=
 explained that =E2=80=9C[n]othing specific happened=E2=80=9D other than =
=E2=80=9C[e]ngagement is increasing and usage is spiking. Our servers are o=
n fire. We are just beginning=C2=A0our journey of massive growth and engage=
ment!=E2=80=9D</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Or the Jira tic=
ket that was like =E2=80=9Cmake more fake users=E2=80=9D:</p><blockquote><p=
 style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A Jira ticket is a project management tool that =
represents a work=C2=A0item that is to be addressed within an organization.=
 Employees create tickets for issues that require attention of others in th=
e company, and the tickets remain open until they are resolved.</p><p style=
=3D"margin: 16px 0;">On August 19, 2021, an IRL employee created a Jira tic=
ket titled =E2=80=9CA series of users for IRL bot that spurs engagement in =
chat.=E2=80=9D The employee sent the ticket to Jacob Shafi, among others. I=
n the ticket, the employee described a plan to =E2=80=9CAdd Fake Users &amp=
; Fake Chats to All Public Groups with Less than 10 People.=E2=80=9D Later,=
 the employee updated the ticket with examples of conversations that bots w=
ould have with one another (=E2=80=9CUser 1: Hey I just joined, what=E2=80=
=99s up?; User 2: Not a whole lot =E2=80=93 a little bored. How=E2=80=99s e=
veryone?; User 1: I=E2=80=99m fine and you?; User 2: Great! What are you do=
ing?=E2=80=9D). The Jira ticket was closed on February 8, 2022.</p></blockq=
uote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I like that even the bots were bored by t=
he fake groups. Eventually IRL=E2=80=99s board noticed the problem and comm=
issioned a report from a consultant, which found that =E2=80=9CIRL had mill=
ions of private groups with identical names, such as =E2=80=98Play Video Ga=
mes=E2=80=99 (4.7 million unique groups), =E2=80=98Book Club=E2=80=99 (4.3 =
million unique groups), and =E2=80=98Call of Duty Squad=E2=80=99 (2.1 milli=
on unique groups).=E2=80=9D No wonder the bots were bored. There are a lot =
of statements in the complaint about SoftBank=E2=80=99s =E2=80=9Crobust due=
 diligence process,=E2=80=9D and I sympathize; user numbers are squishier a=
nd <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/32321698.266412=
/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cudGhlZGlmZi5jby9hcmNoaXZlL2luZm9ybWF0aW9uLWFzLWEtdW5pdmVyc2=
FsLWNvbXBsZW1lbnQtYW5kLXVuaXZlcnNhbC1zdWJzdGl0dXRlLw/607f07ceef4b8524a319a2=
3cB1b672375" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blan=
k" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom=
-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; back=
ground-color: #ccc;"> harder to audit</a> than financial results, and IRL h=
ad no financial results. But I do wonder if anyone at SoftBank spent a few =
days using the app. If you get invited to 100 groups that are all named =E2=
=80=9CPlay Video Games,=E2=80=9D and everyone in the group is like =E2=80=
=9Chey what=E2=80=99s up fellow humans,=E2=80=9D perhaps you start to suspe=
ct something. I guess it was a teen-oriented app, and perhaps you would jus=
t conclude that teens like video games and are boring.</p><p style=3D"margi=
n: 16px 0;">Anyway the consultant concluded that 95% of IRL users were not =
in fact IRL; the board shut down the company and SoftBank=E2=80=99s investm=
ent went to basically zero. It is hard to monetize fake users, or rather, i=
t is hard for <em>SoftBank=C2=A0</em>to monetize fake users; it was fairly =
easy for Shafi. Of the $150 million that SoftBank put in, $7.5 million went=
 to Shafi himself for some of his shares.</p><table class=3D"liveintent-spo=
nsored-content" width=3D"auto" cellpadding=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0">
