ve largely gone down in recent years, but the dividend has stayed stable, a=
nd the company has funded the dividend in part by selling new shares. Becau=
se the dividend is high and stable, and because Icahn is a celebrity, the s=
hares trade at well above net asset value, which means that this trade can =
work: Your stock trades at 3 times NAV, you sell stock for $100, you have $=
100 in new cash, that $100 of cash increases the stock value by $300 (3 tim=
es NAV), and you spend $50 of it paying a dividend to your shareholders to =
keep the stock price high.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But once someone=
 <em>points it out</em>, it doesn=E2=80=99t work as well. The stock is down=
